b'Overgrown hair in need of a buzz? Here are our top tips for a DIY at-home trim!\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
:keycap_digit_one: The Square Silhouette: The overall shape of a standard men\xe2\x80\x99s haircut should suggest the form of a square - but make sure it\xe2\x80\x99s not too boxy with sharp corners! The goal is to make the sides vertical. The top should be evenly horizontal.\xe2\x81\xa3
:keycap_digit_two: Symmetry: Everything you do on the right side of the head, should be done the same on the left side. The top should match as closely as possible the contours of the jawline.\xe2\x81\xa3
:keycap_digit_three: Eyes Centered Vertically: Looking straight at the face, the eyes should be located vertically at the center point from the top of the hair to the bottom of the jaw. The distance from the top of the haircut to the eyes should be the same as the distance from the eyes to the bottom of the jaw.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
Just because you\xe2\x80\x99re in lockdown doesn\xe2\x80\x99t mean you have to rock the overgrown look! Shop hair clippers now.#ConairMan #RespecttheRitual #HairClippers\xe2\x81\xa3'

Learning how to use hot rollers can seem intimidating at first, but now you finally have the time to do it!  Follow these simple steps and you\xe2\x80\x99ll get the hang of it in no-time!\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
:keycap_digit_one: Get ready: Make sure hair is dry, then plug in your hot rollers to heat up while you brush through any knots or tangles. Then, lightly mist hair with a setting spray or comb in a thin layer of mousse.\xe2\x81\xa3
:keycap_digit_two: Section Hair and Roll: Separate a 1-inch section of hair, then place a hot roller near the end of and underneath the section of hair you are holding with your other hand. :keycap_digit_three: Unroll and Set Your Curls Free:  Remove the clips and unroll each roller letting your hair fall freely. Loosen the new curls up a bit with your fingers moving from the roots to the ends.\xe2\x81\xa3
